But I hope that maybe somebody can show me a perspective ,-)<br>
<br>
I'm a well -but by no means uber- equipped Mage.<br>
I'm currently lvl 61 with very little AA (I started playing EQ pretty late).<br>
I can't play very many hours at once usually. Most often I can play 2-3 hour and then have to logout.<br>
I play in a guild that most of you would probably call rather small and we do raid quite a lot. (about 30 active members, almost all lvl 60-62)<br>
I got most important lvl 61 spells (Pet, Blade, belt, dmg bracer,....) and will have all the lvl 61/62 somewhat soon.<br>
<br>
Now...currently I'm falling a bit in a &quot;hole&quot; because I have no clue what to do with my mage beside raiding, which still leaves 80% of my online time uncovered.<br>
Until 60 I could solo just fine and for whatever time I had available.<br>
But now?<br>
<br>
Soloing is no viable choice anymore really.<br>
I'm also so bored of PoD/PoN. I lost roll after roll after roll for parchments (got 61 Air by some trade), now my guild is helping me quite a lot with the spells.<br>
I hardly ever find a group because most often there are already sitting a few mages in the zone.<br>
and even when I'm grouped I'm so bored of getting a AA in 5 or 6 hours when I see people in PoV getting it in 2-3 hours.<br>
<br>
So...I was looking forward to getting flagged for PoV.<br>
Had quite a lot bad luck here (people screwing up, people going LD, failed on endfight ,...). But sometime I will get flaged, no doubt.<br>
And then? In the last days I did a few &quot;/who all Mag lfg&quot; and never ever saw less than 3 Mages /lfg in PoV, among them most often lvl 64/65 Mages.<br>
<br>
So...I will get flaged and then...still won't get exp because I hardly will find a group. Guild groups just happen too seldom. Since we arent too big there are usually some key classes missing (cleric for instance) or people want to do something else or whatever. So most often I have to look for pickup groups....<br>
<br>
Right now I don't even feel like loging my mage and instead play my lowish wizzie.<br>
<br>
It's just too frustrating not finding a group, not knowing what to do...BLAH!<br>
And worst is....as I see it no matter what I do this situation won't ever change. <br>
<br>
I liked my Mage, it was my very first char and I never regretted playing a Mage...until now. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.euphorion.org/sig/euph_new2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sleethr>Sleethr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 263<br> <font color=#333333>(1/7/03 1:27:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8373.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No clue what to look forward to...</span><hr size=1> Just some suggestions in no particular order...<br>
<br>
* Join a bigger guild<br>
* Recruit more people into your guild<br>
* Wizards have it pretty rough too. At least, my guild's wizards seemed to always claim that they had a real hard time finding groups until a raid came up.<br>
* If your guild is always short on clerics, try playing a cleric.<br>
* Play a class that always seems to be needed.  Healer or enchanter seems to get snapped up pretty fast.  They also seem to get pushed thru the trials pretty fast too.<br>
* Get flagged.  I was about ready to quit EQ myself.  Thru bad luck and real life distractions, it took me almost 2 months to get flagged.   It's amazing how much funnier the game has become again by just getting 2 more zones enabled.<br>
* Do the CoD Key quest in PoD.  Decay is a nice zone and it's a Tier 2 zone, so great exp.<br>
* And my personal favorite, try a bard. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Kitty and STA important.<br>
<br>
<br>
Good luck<br>
